Chairman, House of Representatives Committee on Pilgrims Affairs, Abubakar Hassan Nalaraba, yesterday urged Nigerian Muslims to continue to live in harmony and show love to their fellow brothers and sisters regardless of religious, ethnic and political affiliations. Nalaraba, in a statement by his media office, said the celebration of the birthday of Prophet Muhammed is to remind all that the only path to peace and prosperity is to love neighbours. The lawmaker, representing Awe/Doma/Keana Federal Constituency of Nasarawa State, also felicitated Muslims, especially his constituents, on the occasion of Maulud, saying “As we celebrate, let us remember the needy among us and extend love to them.” Maulud: Pray for peaceful elections — Oba of Benin Group holds special Maulud Dogara charges Muslims to pray for Nigeria Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.